d8\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2006|3|26}}\n| AltDate         = -\n| ShortSummary    = \"Bao Zakeruga\" defeats Zeno and causes his book to burn. Before he disappears, Zeno destroys the gem which controls Faudo and tells Zatch if he deserves Bao, he should be able to stop Faudo. Kiyo teleports everyone out of Faudo excluding himself and Zatch using Faudo's system. As Japan nears Faudo's sight, Kiyo plans to use the teleportation device and teleport in front of Faudo and defeat him with \"Bao Zakeruga\", however if the distance between them and Faudo is incorrect, \"Bao Zakeruga\" will be severely weakened. Outside, Sherry and Brago are able to stop Faudo's movement with \"Baber Gravidon\" allowing Kiyo to teleport Zatch and himself out. Using \"Bao Zakeruga\" they destroy Faudo. After an unknown time period, Kiyo and Zatch meet Sherry and Brago in the grassland and prepare to battle each other.\n| LineColor       = FCC\n}}\n|}</onlyinclude>\n\n== Notes ==\n{{reflist|group=\"nb\"}}\n\n== References ==\n;General\n*{{cite web|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5iHCuKgBr?url=http://www.toei-anim.co.jp/tv/GB/episode/list/ |archivedate=July 15, 2009 |url=http://www.toei-anim.co.jp/tv/GB/episode/list/ |title=''Konjiki no Gash Bell!!'' episode list |publisher=[[Toei Animation]] |accessdate=July 14, 2009 |url-status=dead }}\n*{{cite web|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5iHDWSbM8?url=http://www.toei-anim.co.jp/tv/GB/staff.html |archivedate=July 15, 2009 |url=http://www.toei-anim.co.jp/tv/GB/staff.html |title=''Konjiki no Gash Bell!!'' staff list |publisher=[[Toei Animation]] |accessdate=July 14, 2009 |url-status=dead }}\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.ytv.com/programming/shows/zatch_bell/episodes.asp|title=''Zatch Bell!'' episode list|publisher=[[YTV (TV channel)|YTV]]|accessdate=July 23, 2009}}\n\n;Specific\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n{{Zatch Bell navigation}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Zatch Bell! episodes (season 3), List of}}\n[[Category:2005 Japanese television seasons]]\n[[Category:2006 Japanese television seasons]]\n[[Category:Zatch Bell! episode lists|Season 3]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:List of ''Zatch Bell!'' episodes (season 3)}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n  {{All plot|date=September 2012}}\n  {{In-universe|date=September 2012}}\n}}\n[[File:Zatch Bell DVD 3.png|thumb|The cover of the sixteenth DVD compilation for season three of ''Konjiki no Gash Bell!!'' released by [[Shogakukan]] on February 21, 2007]]\nThe third season, known as '''level 3'''<ref name=\"DVD 1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/dp/B000FGG35K/|title=\u91d1\u8272\u306e\u30ac\u30c3\u30b7\u30e5\u30d9\u30eb!! Level 3-1 [DVD]|publisher=[[Amazon.co.jp]]|accessdate=July 30, 2009}}</ref> of the ''[[Zatch Bell!]]'' anime, was directed by Tetsuji Nakamura and Yukio Kaizawa and produced by [[Toei Animation]]. The series, known as {{nihongo3|lit. \"Golden Gash Bell!!|\u91d1\u8272\u306e\u30ac\u30c3\u30b7\u30e5\u30d9\u30eb!!|''Konjiki no Gash Bell!!''}} in Japan, aired on [[Fuji TV]] in Japan.<ref>{{cite web|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5iHDWSbM8?url=http://www.toei-anim.co.jp/tv/GB/staff.html |archivedate=July 15, 2009 |url=http://www.toei-anim.co.jp/tv/GB/staff.html |title=''Konjiki no Gash Bell!!'' staff list |publisher=[[Toei Animation]] |accessdate=July 14, 2009 |url-status=dead }}</ref> The program is based on [[Makoto Raiku]]'s {{Nihongo3|lit. Golden Gash!!|\u91d1\u8272\u306e\u30ac\u30c3\u30b7\u30e5!!|''Konjiki no Gash!!''}} [[manga]] series. The third season adapts the [[List of Zatch Bell! chapters|18th through 22nd]] volumes of the manga and begins to follow an original storyline. The plot follows [[Kiyo Takamine]] and his {{nihongo|''Mamodo''|\u9b54\u7269|''Mamono''|lit. \"demon\"}} partner [[Zatch Bell and Kiyo Takamine|Zatch Bell]]'s journey to stop a giant Mamodo named [[Faudo]] from being released.\n\nThe season began on April 3, 2005 in Japan on Fuji TV, and ended on March 26, 2006.<ref name='episode list'>{{cite web|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5iHCuKgBr?url=http://www.toei-anim.co.jp/tv/GB/episode/list/ |archivedate=July 15, 2009 |url=http://www.toei-anim.co.jp/tv/GB/episode/list/ |title=''Konjiki no Gash Bell!!'' episode list |publisher=[[Toei Animation]] |accessdate=July 14, 2009 |url-status=dead }}</ref> The English adaptation of ''Konjiki no Gash Bell!!'' is licensed by [[Viz Media]], and aired on [[Cartoon Network]] and the Canadian television network [[YTV (TV channel)|YTV]].<ref>{{cite web|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5iTATdaYj?url=http://www.icv2.com/articles/news/5807.html |archivedate=July 23, 2009 |url=http://www.icv2.com/articles/news/5807.html |title='Zatch Bell' Anime on Cartoon Network |publisher=icv2.com |accessdate=July 21, 2009 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5iHFc17xw?url=http://www.channelcanada.com/Article919.html |archivedate=July 15, 2009 |url=http://www.channelcanada.com/Article919.html |title=YTV unveils fall programming highlights |publisher=Channel Canada |accessdate=July 14, 2009 |url-status=dead }}</ref> The episodes were collected into seventeen DVD compilations by [[Shogakukan]] and released between July 7, 2006, and March 7, 2007.<ref name=\"DVD 1\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/dp/B000LW7L54/|title=\u91d1\u8272\u306e\u30ac\u30c3\u30b7\u30e5\u30d9\u30eb!! Level-3 17 [DVD]|publisher=[[Amazon.co.jp]]|language=Japanese|accessdate=July 20, 2009}}</ref> The [[Dub localization|dubbed]] episodes of ''Zatch Bell!'' were discontinued from airing on Cartoon Network after episode 77 on January 20, 2007,<ref>{{cite web |last1=Brian |first1=Hanson |title=January 20th - January 26th - The Click |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/the-click/01-20-07 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=February 22, 2019 |date=January 20, 2007}}</ref> while the Canadian YTV station discontinued the series after episode 104.<ref name=\"Zatch Bell Toonami\">{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2008-08-30/u.s.s-toonami-jetstream-posts-new-zatch-bell-episode|title=U.S.'s Toonami Jetstream Posts New Zatch Bell Episode|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=July 20, 2009}}</ref>\n\nThe episodes use four different pieces of theme music: one opening theme and two closing themes are used in the original Japanese episodes, while one theme is used for the opening and ending in the dubbed episodes. The Japanese opening theme is {{Nihongo3|lit. \"Invisible Wings\"|\u898b\u3048\u306a\u3044\u7ffc|\"Mienai Tsubasa\"}} by Takayoshi Tanimoto.<ref name='Theme 1'>{{cite episode|title=\u65b0\u305f\u306a\u308b\u8105\u5a01 \u98a8\u3092\u8a9e\u308b\u5c11\u5e74 \u30d0\u30aa\u30a6\u62b9\u6bba|episodelink=List_of_Zatch_Bell!_episodes_(Season_3)#ep101|series=\u91d1\u8272\u306e\u30ac\u30c3\u30b7\u30e5\u30d9\u30eb!!|serieslink=Zatch Bell!|station=[[Toei Animation]]|airdate=April 3, 2005|season=3|credits=Director:Tetsuji Nakamura and Yukio Kaizawa}}</ref> The first Japanese ending theme was {{Nihongo3|lit. \"Tomorrow will be better than today\"|\u4eca\u65e5\u3088\u308a\u660e\u65e5\u306f|\"Kyou yori Ashita wa\"}} by Echiura, which was used until episode 125.<ref name='Theme 1'/> The second Japanese ending theme is {{Nihongo3|lit. \"\u2605Play Fever 2005\u2605\"|\u2605\u904aFever 2005\u2605|\"\u2605Aso Fever 2005\u2605\"}} by [[Tomoe Shinohara]] until episode 149.<ref name='Theme 2'>{{cite episode|title=\u623b\u308c\u306a\u3044\u65c5 \u3086\u308c\u308b\u6c7a\u610f \u30d5\u30a1\u30a6\u30fc\u30c9\u306e\u6b63\u4f53|episodelink=List_of_Zatch_Bell!_episodes_(Season_3)#ep126|series=\u91d1\u8272\u306e\u30ac\u30c3\u30b7\u30e5\u30d9\u30eb!!|serieslink=Zatch Bell!|station=[[Toei Animation]]|airdate=October 2, 2004|season=3|credits=Director:Tetsuji Nakamura and Yukio Kaizawa}}</ref> The final episode uses {{Nihongo3|lit. \"Scab\"|\u30ab\u30b5\u30d6\u30bf|\"Kasabuta\"}} by Hidenori Chiwata as its ending theme.<ref name='Theme 3'>{{cite episode|title=\u9003\u3052\u9053\u306a\u3057!! \u5351\u52a3\u306a\u308b\u30be\u30d5\u30a3\u30b9\u518d\u81e8|episodelink=List_of_Zatch_Bell!_episodes_(Season_3)#ep150|series=\u91d1\u8272\u306e\u30ac\u30c3\u30b7\u30e5\u30d9\u30eb!!|serieslink=Zatch Bell!|station=[[Toei Animation]]|airdate=March 26, 2006|season=3|credits=Director:Tetsuji Nakamura and Yukio Kaizawa}}</ref> The English opening theme is \"Follow the Light\", and the ending theme is \"Zatch Bell! Theme\" by [[Thorsten Laewe]] and Greg Prestopino.<ref>{{cite episode|title=A New Menace: The Boy that Speaks to the Wind!|episodelink=List_of_Zatch_Bell!_episodes_(Season_3)#ep101|series=Zatch Bell!|serieslink=Zatch Bell!|station=[[YTV (TV channel)|YTV]]|airdate=November 15, 2008|season=3|credits=Director:Tetsuji Nakamura and Yukio Kaizawa}}</ref>\n\n__FORCETOC__\n\n==Episode list==\n\n<onlyinclude>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" width=\"99%\" style=\"margin: auto\"\n|-\n! style=\"background: #FCC\" width=\"50\" |EP#\n! style=\"background: #FCC\" | Dub Title/Translated Title<br /> Original Title\n! style=\"background: #FCC\" width=\"120\" | Original air date\n! style=\"background: #FCC\" width=\"120\" | English air date\n|-\n{{Episode list/sublist\n| 1               = List of Zatch Bell! episodes (season 3)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 101\n| Title           = A New Menace: The Boy that Speaks to the Wind!\n| TranslitTitle   = Aratanaru ky\u014di Kaze wo gataru sh\u014dnen Baou massatsu!\n| NativeTitle     = \u65b0\u305f\u306a\u308b\u8105\u5a01 \u98a8\u3092\u8a9e\u308b\u5c11\u5e74 \u30d0\u30aa\u30a6\u62b9\u6bba!\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2005|4|3}}\n| AltDate         = November 15, 2008\n| ShortSummary    = In a deserted area, a large structure rises from the ground. Elsewhere, a Mamodo named [[Ted and Jido|Ted]] and his partner Jido arrive in town, Ted searching for a job to pay for lodging. Ted wanders into a park, after failing to find a job, and finds a box that he plans to lodge in. When he looks inside it, however, he finds Zatch. They proceed to get into an argument and begin fighting. They then become friends. Jido finds Ted and Zatch and reprimands him for not searching for a job. Ted tells Jido they can stay at Zatch's place. Once there, He tells Jido he is not interested in fighting, and Jido replies he does not as well and that Ted is not aiming to become the Mamodo king. That night a Mamodo named [[Arth and Ellie|Arth]] and his partner [[Arth and Ellie|Ellie]] challenge Zatch and Kiyo to a battle, telling Zatch and Kiyo that they are the users of Bao and the menace of the Mamodo world that appeared in the human world. Arth overpowers Zatch and prepares to deliver a final attack but is interrupted by the appearance of Jido and Ted.\n| LineColor       = FCC\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist\n| 1               = List of Zatch Bell! episodes (season 3)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 102\n| Title           = The Beginning of a Friendship, and the End of a Spell?\n| TranslitTitle   = Tsukiyomaro no d\u014dran Y\u016bjo no kobushi \u0100su ichigeki hissatsu!\n| NativeTitle     = \u6708\u591c\u306e\u52d5\u4e71 \u53cb\u60c5\u306e\u62f3 \u30a2\u30fc\u30b9\u4e00\u6483\u5fc5\u6bba!\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2005|4|10}}\n| AltDate         = November 22, 2008\n| ShortSummary    = While [[Zeno and Dufort|Zeno]] is at the location of the mysterious structure, Ted continues battling Arth gaining the advantage. Kiyo realizes that Arth's sword absorbs energy which explains Zatch's exhaustion from the battle. Jido casts a spell and Ted's strength and speed increase. Jido reveals Ted's spells increase his power one level at a time but takes time to cast. Ellie decides to use a higher-level spell giving Arth the advantage against Ted.\n| LineColor       = FCC\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist\n| 1               = List of Zatch Bell! episodes (season 3)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 103\n| Title           = Ted's Blues: The Girl in the Wind\n| Trans