 the battle, Ellie tells Souza the world's fate depends on those two. Sunbeam tells Souza that everyone share the same feeling of wanting to protect the world. Souza complies to work with Sunbeam. Ponygon and Cardio working together, defeat Jedon and Fango. Apollo and Dr. Riddles launch Ted and Jido into Faudo. At that moment however, an unknown Mamodo pair also enter Faudo's mouth.\n| LineColor       = FCC\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist\n| 1               = List of Zatch Bell! episodes (season 3)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 142\n| Title           = Sealed room. Aleshie's fight. Destiny once more!\n| TranslitTitle   = Tozasareta heya Arishie no tatakai Innen futatabi!\n| NativeTitle     = \u9589\u3056\u3055\u308c\u305f\u90e8\u5c4b \u30a2\u30ea\u30b7\u30a8\u306e\u6226 \u56e0\u7e01\u518d\u3073!\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2006|1|29}}\n| AltDate         = -\n| ShortSummary    = Kiyo's group continue on and run into Faudo's minions, the Mamodo Gyaron and his book owner Harry. Aleshie and Riya volunteer to battle them while allowing the rest to rest and recover their energy. Aleshie and Riya gain the upper hand and as they prepare to defeat Gyaron, Rodeaux and Chita appear holding Li-en hostage. Kiyo and Zatch separate them from Li-en and allows Aleshie and Riya to defeat their opponents. Gyaron's book is burned in the process. They threaten to hurt Li-en but Kiyo's team reveal they found out that the Li-en in their captures is a fake. Li-en is revealed to be Zarchim in disguise and he then destroys Rodeux' book. Using a spell, he restrains everyone except Aleshie and Riya and tells Aleshie that one of them shall disappear.\n| LineColor       = FCC\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist\n| 1               = List of Zatch Bell! episodes (season 3)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 143\n| Title           = Burn Up Life. Warrior Alishie. The Conclusion!? Zaruchimu\n| TranslitTitle   = Inochi wo moyase Ikusabito Arishie Ketchaku!? Zaruchimu\n| NativeTitle     = \u547d\u3092