{"title_page": "John Karna", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2019}}\n{{BLP sources|date=April 2016}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = John Karna\n| birth_name = John Timothy Karna\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1992|11|18}}\n| occupation = Actor\n| years_active = 2012\u2013present\n| birth_place = [[Houston|Houston, Texas]], U.S.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.slackerwood.com/node/4166|title=Texas at SXSW 2014: John Karna, 'Premature'|author=Mike Saulters|work=Slackerwood|date=March 19, 2014|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117024827/http://www.slackerwood.com/node/4166|archivedate=November 17, 2015}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''John Timothy Karna''' (born November 18, 1992)<ref>{{cite tweet|number = 799782481754894336|title = My homies, the birthday love is truly humbling. Many many thanks. Now go have yourselves a lovely Friday night!!! \ud83d\udcaf\ud83d\udcaf\ud83d\udcaf\ud83c\udf89\ud83c\udfc4\ud83c\udffc|last = Karna|first = John|accessdate = April 25, 2019|date = November 18, 2016|user = johnny_k}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet|number=1066454513920499713|title=Hey bababooie 26 is feelin good thanks for the memories gang \ud83c\udf40\u270c\ufe0f! |user=johnny_k|last=Karna|first=John|accessdate=July 20, 2019|date=November 24, 2018}}</ref> is an American actor. He is known for his role as Noah Foster in the first two seasons of the [[MTV]] [[Slasher film|slasher]] television series ''[[Scream (TV series)|Scream]]'', based on the [[Scream (franchise)|film series of the same name]]. He is also known for appearing in the films ''[[Bindlestiffs]]'' (2012) and ''[[Premature (film)|Premature]]'' (2014).\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Bindlestiffs]]''\n| John Woo\n|\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Premature (film)|Premature]]''\n| Rob Crabbe\n|\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Sugar Mountain (film)|Sugar Mountain]]''\n| Josh Miller\n| \n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Lady Bird (film)|Lady Bird]]''\n| Greg Anrue\n| \n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2014\n| data-sort-value=\"Neighbors, The\" | ''[[The Neighbors (2012 TV series)|The Neighbors]]''\n| Hank\n| Episode: \"You've Lost That Larry Feeling\"\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Law & Order: Special Victims Unit]]''\n| [[Holden March]]\n| Episode: \"[[Law & Order: Special Victims Unit (season 16)#ep347|Holden's Manifesto]]\"\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Modern Family]]''\n| Alec\n| Episode: \"[[Strangers in the Night (Modern Family)|Strangers in the Night]]\"\n|-\n| 2015\u20132016\n| ''[[Scream (TV series)|Scream]]''\n| Noah Foster\n| Main role (seasons 1\u20132)\n|-\n| 2016\n|  ''[[Chicago Fire (TV series)|Chicago Fire]]''\n| Alan\n| Episode: \"I Held Her Hand\"\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[Dirty John (TV series)|Dirty John]]''\n| Jimmy\n| Episode: \"Approachable Dreams\"\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Valley of the Boom]]''\n|[[Marc Andreessen]]\n| Main role<ref>{{cite web |url=http://deadline.com/2018/03/valley-of-the-boom-bradley-whitford-steve-zahn-lamorne-norris-nat-geos-silicon-valley-themed-limited-series-1202339218/ |title=''Valley Of The Boom'': Bradley Whitford, Steve Zahn & Lamorne Morris To Star In Nat Geo's Silicon Valley-Themed Limited Series |first1=Nellie |last1=Andreeva |first2=Denise |last2=Petski |date=March 16, 2018 |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |accessdate=March 17, 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180317105238/http://deadline.com/2018/03/valley-of-the-boom-bradley-whitford-steve-zahn-lamorne-norris-nat-geos-silicon-valley-themed-limited-series-1202339218/ |archivedate=March 17, 2018}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Web===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''Scream: If I Die''\n| Noah Foster\n| Episode: \"Welcome to the Morgue\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2882198/scream-last-words-if-i-die/ |title=Famous Last Words: Wa