eague]], 25 August 2011\n*Record [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] win: 4\u20130 vs. [[RCD Mallorca]] (a), 16 October 2001\n*Record [[Revierderby]] win: 6\u20131 vs. Borussia Dortmund (h), Bundesliga, 10 December 1985\n*Record defeat: 0\u201311 vs. [[Borussia M\u00f6nchengladbach]] (a), Bundesliga, 7 January 1967\n'''League'''\n*Most league wins in a season: 24 ([[Bundesliga]], [[1971\u201372 Bundesliga|1971\u201372]], 34 games)\n*Most league goals scored in a season: 95 ([[2. Bundesliga]], [[1983\u201384 2. Bundesliga|1983\u201384]], 38 games)\n*Most Bundesliga goals scored in a season: 77 ([[1976\u201377 Bundesliga|1976\u201377]], 34 games)\n*Fewest league goals conceded in a season: 29 (2. Bundesliga, [[1990\u201391 2. Bundesliga|1990\u201391]], 38 games)\n*Fewest Bundesliga goals conceded in a season: 31 each ([[2005\u201306 Bundesliga|2005\u201306]] and [[2009\u201310 Bundesliga|2009\u201310]], 34 games)\n*Most consecutive league wins: 6 each (Bundesliga, [[2004\u201305 Bundesliga|2004\u201305]] md 7\u201312, [[2006\u201307 Bundesliga|2006\u201307]] md 16\u201321, [[2017\u201318 Bundesliga|2017\u201318]] md  23\u201328 and 2. Bundesliga, [[1990\u201391 2. Bundesliga|1990\u201391]] md 3\u20138)\n*Most consecutive league matches without a defeat: 14 (Bundesliga, [[1976\u201377 Bundesliga|1976\u201377]] md 29 \u2013 [[1977\u201378 Bundesliga|1977\u201378]] md 8)\n*Most consecutive league matches without a defeat within a season: 13 each (Bundesliga, [[1997\u201398 Bundesliga|1997\u201398]] md 16\u201328 and [[2006\u201307 Bundesliga|2006\u201307]] md 10\u201322)\n\n===Pre-Bundesliga era===\n'''Matches'''\n*Record league win: 20\u20130 vs. SpVgg Herten (a), [[Landesliga Westfalen]], 23 February 1947\n*Record league home win: 15\u20131 vs. Union Recklinghausen, [[Gauliga Westfalen]], 16 February 1936\n*Record [[Oberliga West (1947\u201363)|Oberliga West]] win: 8\u20130 vs. [[Borussia M\u00f6nchengladbach]] (h), 24. September 1950\n*Record [[List of German football champions|German championship]] win: 16\u20130 vs. CSC 03 Kassel (h), 16 June 1940\n*Record German championship final win: 9\u20130 vs. [[FC Admira Wacker M\u00f6dling|Admira Vienna]] (in Berlin), 18. June 1939\n*Record [[DFB-Pokal]] win: 13\u20130 vs. VfvB Alsum (a), 20. August 1939\n*Record European win: 5\u20132 vs. [[Kj\u00f8benhavns Boldklub|KB Copenhagen]] (h), [[European Cup]], 18 September 1958\n*Record [[Revierderby]] win: 10\u20130 vs. Borussia Dortmund (h), Gauliga Westfalen, 20 October 1940\n\n'''League'''\n*Most league wins in a season: 21 ([[Gauliga Westfalen]], [[1940\u201341 Gauliga|1940\u201341]], 22 games)\n*Most league goals scored in a season: 103 (Gauliga Westfalen, [[1936\u201337 Gauliga|1936\u201337]], 18 games)\n*Fewest league goals conceded in a season: 10 each (Gauliga Westfalen, [[1934\u201335 Gauliga|1934\u201335]], [[1937\u201338 Gauliga|1937\u201338]], [[1941\u201342 Gauliga|1941\u201342]] and [[1943\u201344 Gauliga|1943\u201344]], 18 games each)\n*Most consecutive league wins: 26 (Gauliga Westfalen, [[1935\u201336 Gauliga|1935\u201336]] md 4 \u2013 [[1936\u201337 Gauliga|1936\u201337]] md 11)\n*Most consecutive league wins with a season: 16 (Gauliga Westfalen, [[1942\u201343 Gauliga|1942\u201343]] md 3\u201318)\n*Most consecutive league matches without a defeat: 84 (Gauliga Westfalen, [[1934\u201335 Gauliga|1934\u201335]] md 18 \u2013 [[1939\u201340 Gauliga|1939\u201340]] md 11)\n\n==Honours==\n{|class=wikitable\n!Competition!!width=25|#!!Years\n|-\n|bgcolor=efefef align=center colspan=3|'''International title'''\n|-\n|[[UEFA Europa League|UEFA Cup]]||align=center|1||[[1996\u201397 UEFA Cup|1997]]\n|-\n|bgcolor=efefef align=center colspan=3|'''National titles'''\n|-\n|[[List of German football champions|German Championship]]||align=center|7||[[1934 German football championship|1934]], [[1935 German football championship|1935]], [[1937 German football championship|1937]], [[1939 German football championship|1939]], [[1940 German