|{{0}}8 ''(11)''||{{0}}3 {{0}}''(6)''||{{0}}'''93''' ''(119)''||0.78\n|-\n|10||align=\"left\"|{{sortname|Hermann|Nattk\u00e4mper}}||{{sort|C|MF}}|||1930\u20131936||{{0}}29 {{0}}''(49)''||\u2013||{{0}}45 ''(33)''||10 ''(30)''||{{0}}0 {{0}}''(6)''||{{0}}6 ''(10)''||{{0}}'''90''' ''(128)''||0.70\n|}\n{{notelist}}\n\n====Other records====\n'''Youngest and oldest'''\n* Youngest player: [[Bernhard Klodt]] \u2013 16 years, 83 days (17 January 1943, Gauliga Westfalen)\n* Youngest goalscorer: [[Bernhard Klodt]] \u2013 16 years, 83 days (17 January 1943, Gauliga Westfalen)\n* Oldest player: [[Ernst Kuzorra]] \u2013 43 years, 92 days (16 January 1949, Oberliga West)\n* Oldest goalscorer: [[Ernst Kuzorra]] \u2013 41 years, 333 days (14 September 1947, Oberliga West)\n\n'''Goals'''\n* Most goals in a season in all competitions: [[Hermann Eppenhoff]] \u2013 42 (1940\u201341)\n* Most league goals in a season: [[Ernst Kuzorra]] \u2013 34 (1929\u201330, Gauliga Ruhr)\n* Most Gauliga Westfalen goals in a season: [[Hermann Eppenhoff]] \u2013 28 ([[1940\u201341 Gauliga|1940\u201341]])\n* Most Oberliga West goals in a season: Hans Kleina \u2013 23 ([[1950\u201351 Oberliga#Oberliga West|1950\u201351]])\n* Most German championship goals in a season: [[Hermann Eppenhoff]] \u2013 13 ([[1941 German football championship|1941]])\n* Most goals scored in a match: [[Herbert Burdenski]] \u2013 8 (23 February 1947, Landesliga Westfalen)\n'''Internationals'''\n* First international cap as a Schalke 04 player: [[Ernst Kuzorra]] \u2013 20 November 1927\n* Most international caps as a Schalke 04 player: [[Fritz Szepan]] \u2013 34 (1929 \u2013 1939)\n* Most international goals as a Schalke 04 player: [[Adolf Urban]] \u2013 11 (1935 \u2013 1942)\n* World Cup winner: [[Bernhard Klodt]] ([[1954 FIFA World Cup|1954]])\n\n===All time===\n\n====Most appearances====\n[[File:Klaus Fichtel.jpeg|thumb|upright|<center>[[Klaus Fichtel]]</center>]]\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable nowrap\" style=\"text-align: cente